This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for visual tracking, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically deals with the use of deep learning models for tracking in thermal infrared (TIR) images, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes the use of image-to-image translation models, which is a popular area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve tracking objects in video sequences, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with the generation of synthetic data, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
